Overall_Design: AMPK activation by GSK621 induces cell death in acute myeloid leukemia. Surprisingly, we found that mTORC1 inhibition with rapamycin protects cells against GSK621-induced cytotoxicity. A genome-wide gene expression assay was performed to understand the molecular basis of this phenotype.

Characteristic: Rapamycin- then GSK621-treated MOLM-14 cells, rep1
